{"timestamp": "2025-12-07 06:55:29.227793", "event": "llm_end", "text": "Troubleshooting Diagnosis Report\n\nScope\n- Verify end-to-end reachability for user hosts to infrastructure and server farm.\n- Validate OSPF control-plane health and routing.\n- Check name resolution and HTTP service access (direct web servers and load balancer).\n- Confirm backend web servers are not reachable directly from user subnets (segmentation by design).\n\nSummary Assessment\n- The network is operating normally. No critical anomalies were found.\n- OSPF adjacencies are established across cores, distributions, and server access, and routes are correctly learned.\n- DNS resolution and HTTP access to web services (including the load balancer web99.local) function from multiple host subnets.\n- Backend web servers are not reachable directly from hosts, as intended.\n\nEvidence and Findings\n\n1) Host IP/DHCP and Default Gateway\n- host_1_1_1_1: 10.1.1.12/24 via 10.1.1.1 (dynamic DHCP, valid_lft ~46s).\n- host_2_1_1_1: 10.2.1.17/24 via 10.2.1.1 (dynamic DHCP, valid_lft ~36s).\n- Both are correctly configured; leases are short but active.\n\n2) Reachability and Latency (ICMP)\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to dns_server (10.200.0.2): 0% loss, avg ~2.67 ms.\n- From host_2_1_1_1 to dns_server: 0% loss, avg ~2.12 ms.\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to load_balancer (10.200.0.7): 0% loss, avg ~2.47 ms.\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to web_server_0 (10.200.0.3) and web_server_1 (10.200.0.4): 0% loss; occasional first-packet RTT spike (e.g., 11–14 ms) then steady ~1.5–2.4 ms.\n- Broad lab-wide ping sampling (get_reachability) across many subnets shows 0% packet loss and low, stable RTTs end-to-end, indicating healthy data-plane connectivity across OSPF areas.\n\n3) HTTP Service Checks (curl)\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to http://web99.local (load balancer): \n  - name lookup ~2–25 ms, connect ~4–6 ms, TTFB ~0.19–0.25 s, total ~0.996–1.036 s (3 runs).\n- From host_2_1_1_1 to http://web99.local:\n  - name lookup ~2–10 ms, connect ~4–6 ms, TTFB ~0.216 s, total ~1.018–1.024 s (3 runs).\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to http://web0.local (direct server):\n  - name lookup ~6–75 ms, connect ~9–78 ms, TTFB ~0.296–0.308 s, total ~1.101–1.112 s (2 runs).\n- Interpretation: DNS works and connections are quick; TTFB is consistent (~0.2–0.3 s). Total ~1.0–1.1 s likely reflects application content/behavior rather than network congestion. No evidence of network-induced delay.\n\n4) OSPF Control Plane Health\n- Neighbors:\n  - router_core_1: Full with core_2, core_3, and multiple downstreams.\n  - router_core_2 and router_core_3: Full with peers and relevant downstreams.\n  - router_dist_1_1 and router_dist_2_1: Full with upstream cores.\n  - server_access_router: Full with core_3 (172.16.0.22/31).\n- Neighbor uptimes ~1.3–1.8 minutes (suggest recent restart or topology bring-up) but currently stable; no stuck or partial states observed.\n\n5) Routing Tables (sampled)\n- server_access_router:\n  - 10.200.0.0/24 directly connected (br0).\n  - All 10.x/24 user subnets learned via OSPF through 172.16.0.22 (core_3).\n- router_core_1:\n  - 10.200.0.0/24 reachable via core_3 (172.16.0.3). Multiple inter-core/inter-dist routes present with equal-cost/alt paths where applicable.\n- router_dist_1_1:\n  - 10.1.1.0/24 directly connected (br0).\n  - 10.200.0.0/24 via 172.16.0.6 (core_1).\n- Interpretation: Control-plane distribution aligns with the described topology; server farm networks are advertised and reachable end-to-end.\n\n6) Security/Segmentation – Backend Web Servers\n- From host_1_1_1_1 to backend_web_0 (20.200.0.2):\n  - Destination Net Unreachable, generated by default gateway 10.1.1.1.\n- Interpretation: The backend segment is not reachable from user subnets, which matches the design requirement to prevent direct host access to backends.\n\nAnomalies or Irregularities Observed\n- None impacting connectivity or routing.\n- Minor notes:\n  - OSPF neighbor uptimes are short (minutes), indicating recent convergence/restarts; currently stable.\n  - Occasional first ICMP probe RTT spikes to some servers (one-off 10–14 ms) but subsequent probes are normal; no loss observed.\n  - DHCP lease timers on hosts appear short (tens of seconds remaining at time of query); leases are valid and functional in the lab context.\n  - HTTP total times consistently ~1.0–1.1 s with TTFB ~0.2–0.3 s; this looks application-side and consistent across paths, not a network error.\n\nConclusion\n- No network anomalies detected. The OSPF control plane is converged and routes are correctly propagated. User hosts can reach DNS and web services in 10.200.0.0/24 via OSPF, and the load balancer web99.local is accessible and serving. Backend web servers are not directly reachable from user subnets, as intended by policy. Overall network health is good, with no faulty devices or routing issues identified at this time.", "generation_info": {"finish_reason": "stop", "logprobs": null}, "invalid_tool_calls": [], "usage_metadata": {"input_tokens": 46305, "output_tokens": 5098, "total_tokens": 51403, "input_token_details": {"audio": 0, "cache_read": 46080}, "output_token_details": {"audio": 0, "reasoning": 3712}}}
